text: It's a copy of the math test
I am going to take this Thursday.
I found it in the library...in the trash can!
What are you going to do with it?
I think I'm going to use it to study.
I haven't been doing very well in math this year.
If I get a good grade, my parents will be proud.
Would they be proud if they knew you cheated?
The book of Proverbs says that
"Good people are guided by their honesty,
but crooks who lie and cheat will ruin themselves.‚Äù
I think you need to take this test back to the teacher,
tell them you found it and did not use it.
That would be the honest thing to do.
I will take it to the teacher right away,
then I will start studying. Thanks Jon!
